}{}$S = S_n \cup S_b$\end{document}</tex-math></inline-formula> where <italic>S<sub>n</sub></italic> and <italic>S<sub>b</sub></italic> indicate the set of characters for non-branching and branching stem structures, respectively). Then, the BEAR alphabet β is defined as <inline-formula><tex-math id="M3">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
\usepackage{amsmath}
\usepackage{wasysym} 
\usepackage{amsfonts} 
