    <sec id="SEC2-7">
      <title>Secondary structure recovery and structural distance</title>
      <p>In order to verify the ability of MBR to recover secondary structure information, that is to say the ability of the method to correctly align conserved secondary structures, we computed the structural conservation index (SCI) (<xref rid="B45" ref-type="bibr">45</xref>) of the resulting pairwise alignments. SCI is defined as the ratio between the consensus minimum free energy (MFE) of the consensus alignment normalized by the average MFE or the single sequences:
